wikipedia_page.main: David Thomas Ivor  Jenkins (3 June 1929 – 16 September 2014) was Archdeacon of Westmorland and Furness from 1999 until 1999.Jenkins was educated at King's College London and ordained in 1953. After a curacy at Rugby he held incumbencies in Coventry and Carlisle. He was a Canon Residentiary at Carlisle Cathedral from 1991 to 1995.
